-{"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-mfe0","title":"[bug] mindspec next: positional bead-ID silently ignored on claim path, claims wrong bead (GH #146.1)","description":"GitHub issue #146 (claim #1). `mindspec next \u003cbead-id\u003e` WITHOUT --emit-only drops the positional arg, prints \"Defaulting to first item\", and claims the WRONG bead (creates its worktree, sets in_progress, moves the state cursor). next --help says it \"Accepts an optional positional bead ID\" but that only applies under --emit-only.\n\nVERIFIED still present on main:\n- cmd/mindspec/next.go (~L38-59): positional args passed to runEmitOnly() ONLY; claim path ignores them.\n- claim path (~L203-216) calls next.SelectWork(items, pick) using only --pick; internal/next/select.go returns items[0] by default.\n\nFIX: honor a positional bead-ID on the claim path (claim THAT bead or error if not ready), or if unsupported outside --emit-only, make passing it warn/error rather than silently claim the first. NOTE (per 097 R3): bead order comes from STRUCTURED work_chunks.depends_on, not prose **Depends on** — plan template/docs should make that explicit so authors don't expect prose deps to gate readiness. Domains: cli/next.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:52Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:52Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
