 {"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-gpoq","title":"Scaffold adr_citations: into the plan.md frontmatter template + name the key in the adr-citations WARN (GH #145.4)","description":"GitHub issue #145 (bonus). Clearing the adr-citations WARN requires the frontmatter key adr_citations: (a list of ADR IDs), but it is absent from the scaffolded plan.md and the WARN message names only the check id \"adr-citations\", not the key. Reporter guessed adrs: / a ## Cited ADRs section — neither worked.\n\nVERIFIED on main:\n- internal/approve/spec.go scaffoldPlan (~L228-263): frontmatter has status/spec_id/version, no adr_citations.\n- internal/validate/plan.go (~L141) WARN text does not name the adr_citations key (key is defined at ~L29).\n\nFIX: add `adr_citations: []` (with a one-line example comment) to the scaffolded plan.md frontmatter, and name the exact key in the adr-citations WARN message. Domains: approve (scaffold) + validate (warn text).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:59Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-16T20:36:03Z","closed_at":"2026-06-16T20:36:03Z","close_reason":"Implemented + merged via spec 100-ownership-gate-resolution (PR #148, nekh.1/.2/.3)","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
 {"_type":"issue","id":"mindspec-3cfr","title":"[bug] mindspec adr show/list read the main worktree only, inconsistent with adr create + worktree-aware validator (GH #145.2/.3)","description":"GitHub issue #145 (points #2 and #3). adr show/list resolve via workspace.FindRoot (-\u003e main repo root), so editing an ADR in the active spec WORKTREE does not change `mindspec adr show` output, while `mindspec adr create` (FindLocalRoot) writes to the worktree. This split made the reporter edit ADR-0001 repeatedly thinking the Domain(s) parse was broken (point #3) — but it was the main-vs-worktree split: they edited the worktree copy, adr show read main (empty).\n\nVERIFIED on main:\n- cmd/mindspec/adr.go: adr show (~L138) and adr list (~L97) use workspace.FindRoot (main); adr create (~L32) uses workspace.FindLocalRoot (worktree). The plan VALIDATOR is already worktree-aware (adrStoreForSpec, fixed in ew79) — so the gate works; only the inspection CLIs are main-only.\n- Point #3: internal/adr/parse.go (~L74) strings.Contains accepts BOTH `**Domain(s)**:` and `- **Domain(s)**:`, so parsing is NOT actually format-sensitive — but there is no test for the non-list form and templates only emit the list form.\n\nFIX: make adr show/list resolve from the active worktree (overlay like the validator), or clearly document/emit that ADRs are main-worktree-global. Add a parse test for the non-list `**Domain(s)**:` form to lock current behavior. Domains: cli/adr (+ adr).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"richardmaxsteel@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-15T16:58:58Z","created_by":"mrmaxsteel","updated_at":"2026-06-16T20:36:01Z","closed_at":"2026-06-16T20:36:01Z","close_reason":"Implemented + merged via spec 100-ownership-gate-resolution (PR #148, nekh.1/.2/.3)","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
